toxicity such as fever, rash, itching, anorexia, nausea, vomiting, fatigue, malaise, right upper quadrant pain, dark urine, pale stools, and jaundice.', 'Synergism', 'Gemfibrozil, Evinacumab, Evolocumab, Probucol, Dextrothyroxine, Cholestyramine, Clofibrate, Colestipol, Ezetimibe, Bempedoic acid, Colesevelam, More', 'Pertuzumab, Cetuximab, Avelumab, Panitumumab, Obinutuzumab, Bevacizumab, Necitumumab, Dostarlimab, Ramucirumab, Atezolizumab, Amivantamab, More', 'Moderate', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/47110/', '[1] "Product Information. Adcetris (brentuximab vedotin)." Seattle Genetics Inc, Bothell, WA.[2] "Product Information. Accolate (zafirlukast)." Zeneca Pharmaceuticals, Wilmington, DE.', 1767369485);
